newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soy losses pressure soyoil, soymeal futures.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soy losses pressure soyoil, soymeal futures.

text.p: CBOT soy product futures were lower at midsession Friday, under pressure mostly from heavy losses in CBOT soybeans, traders said.
CBOT July soybeans posted losses as large as 10-1/2 cents per bushel Friday morning, under pressure from technical weakness and a drop in the pace of the weekly U.S. soybean crush, traders said.
Supportive factors in soyoil trade included continued talk of heavy Chinese interest in South American vegetable oil markets, traders said.
"South American oil basis is firm again," a trader said. "It's up on rumors that China is looking to buy more oil."

The drop in CBOT soymeal prices encouraged some buying from end-users in cash markets, dealers said. However, many livestock feeders are turning to less expensive feed alternatives such as grass, traders said.
In early soyoil trading Produce Grain sold 900 lots July. In soymeal trade, Prudential Securities sold 300 lots July and Refco and Rosenthal each sold 100 July, sources said.
At 1139 CDT, soyoil was down 0.06 to 0.13 cent per lb., and soymeal was down 0.50 to $3.10 per lb.
